# Auto-loaded by direnv when entering this directory.
#
# Layers two sources of environment on top of each other:
#   1. source_up — inherits KUBECONFIG from the repo-root .envrc so
#      the helm provider can talk to the cluster. (Without this,
#      entering terraform/ would replace the parent's env entirely
#      and we'd lose KUBECONFIG.)
#   2. source_env — pulls Scaleway access keys (as AWS_* env vars)
#      from ~/.config/paulin-infra/scaleway.env (chmod 600, outside
#      the repo) so the S3 backend can read/write tofu state.
#
# This file contains no secrets — it's safe and intended to be committed.
# Anyone cloning the repo learns from it that they need to set up
# direnv + the secrets file before running tofu.

source_up
source_env ~/.config/paulin-infra/scaleway.env
